You are attaching 9420 event listeners (three for each county). A better solution would be to do the equivalent of delegate in jQuery:<p><pre><code>  var counties = map.append('g');

  counties.attr('class', 'counties')
	  .selectAll('path')
	    .data(countylines.features)
	  .enter().append('path')
	    .attr('d', path);

  counties.on('mouseover', function(){
           if (d3.event.target.tagName == "path")
              showCaption();
        })
	.on('mouseout', function() {
           if (d3.event.target.tagName != "path")
	    	caption.html(starter);
	    });
</code></pre>
You also don't need to repeat the process on mousemove, that triggers dozens of events per second for what mouseover and mouseout already accomplished.<p>Try it out, I'm sure it will feel snappier.
